re. Over the course of the game, we should see initial exploratory offers that are somewhat unappealing to others, followed by adjustment once players learn who really values which chip colors from the pattern of acceptances and rejections.\n\nGiven the personas, butterfly is numerate, risk- and uncertainty-averse, and fairly cooperative, so she will likely propose trades that give herself a clear gain and hope others still see them as worthwhile. Kangaroo is analytical, willing to search broadly, and especially motivated to convert blue into red when possible, but will be careful not to sacrifice green. Squid, with the highest blue value and strong cooperative orientation, is the most likely to propose clean efficiency-enhancing trades involving red-for-blue swaps and to accept slightly unbalanced offers that still give her a clear gain. Overall, the most natural trade pattern is a kangaroo–squid red–blue exchange, potentially with butterfly occasionally using green to take advantage of small valuation gaps as a middleman. We forecast a game where the clearest surplus opportunities between kangaroo and squid are realized by mid-game once their preferences are partially revealed through responses, while some early butterfly proposals are declined as too one-sided or misaligned with others' private values.",
