 BLUE-for-RED or BLUE-for-GREEN deals, sometimes accepting modest but safe gains to avoid ending the game with purely initial holdings. Because there are only nine proposal turns and everyone is moderately uncertainty averse, they are unlikely to hold out for perfectly efficient trades; instead, we should see a small number of conservative, win–win exchanges, mostly involving mouse offloading RED in exchange for GREEN, and possibly dog or owl paying with a few BLUE when the exchange is still net-positive for them.",
